        "title": "Java using regex to replace At position 4, 5 and 6 words from a string",
        "body": "<p>Can i use a regex to replace the 4th, 5th, 6th words with * from a string ?<\/p>\n\n<p>Actually i do this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Test\n{\n    public static void main( String[] args )\n    {\n        StringBuilder myName = new StringBuilder(\"AD-BJR5U\");\n        myName.setCharAt(3, '*');\n        myName.setCharAt(4, '*');\n        myName.setCharAt(5, '*');\n        System.out.println(myName);\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><strong><em>Input:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>AD-BJR5U<\/p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Output:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>AD-***5U<\/p>\n",
